'''iron oxide''' (''Plural:'' '''iron oxides''')
{{wikipedia}}

#(Chemistry) The compound obtained by the reaction of oxygen on [[iron]]. Either iron (II) oxide  (old term ferrous oxide, checmical formula FeO) or iron (III) oxide (old term ferric oxide, chemical formula Fe<sub>2</sub>O<sub>3</sub>).  Generally known as ''[[rust]]''.